{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Building a macOS VM Manager"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Compose the Spooktacular libraries into a first-class Mac app.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BuildingAMacOSVMManager"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article walks through the layered structure of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular SwiftUI app so you can build something comparable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without repeating the architectural decisions we already settled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app target depends on three Swift packages in this repo:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SpookCore"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — pure Swift domain types. No AppKit, no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization"},{"type":"text","text":", no networking. Use it for models, enums,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and protocol “ports” that describe what the app needs without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"committing to a concrete transport."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookApplication","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — use cases and services that combine"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain types into workflows (RBAC evaluation, tenant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isolation, runner-pool orchestration)."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineCo